   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Response to Internally Displaced People</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since the beginning of April 2015, approximately 21,000 Burundians, mostly women
and children, had fled to Rwanda having experienced intimidation and threats of
violence linked to the planned June 26th Presidential election.
JOA granted Tearfund &#xA3;28,800 to assist refugees with the provision of food and non-food items, sanitary kits and
clothing and UNICEF &#xA3;30,000 towards water, sanitation, health and nutrition supplies and child protection for children
and families.</narrative>
  </description>
